-Where are you?

5
00:00:56,161 --> 00:00:57,912
Where are we going right now?

6
00:00:57,996 --> 00:00:58,830
The gym!

7
00:00:58,913 --> 00:01:01,124
-Se-ah and Ha-joon are in the gym.
-Se-ah?

8
00:01:01,207 --> 00:01:02,625
The gym!

9
00:01:02,709 --> 00:01:05,461
I'm blind in one eye, so I'm a bit slow.
Hey, wait up!

10
00:01:26,941 --> 00:01:28,067
Na-ri.

11
00:01:28,151 --> 00:01:29,110
Hey, Lim Na-ri.

12
00:01:32,113 --> 00:01:33,740
-How could you?
-Se-ah, watch out!

13
00:01:41,623 --> 00:01:42,624
Ha-joon!

14
00:01:46,169 --> 00:01:47,378
-Which way?
-Not that way!

15
00:01:47,462 --> 00:01:48,546
-Go left!
-Where?

16
00:01:48,630 --> 00:01:49,756
Go!

17
00:01:49,839 --> 00:01:50,715
-Up there?
-Go!

18
00:01:50,798 --> 00:01:52,133
Ha-joon, are you okay?

19
00:01:53,134 --> 00:01:54,677
Lim Na-ri, are you insane?

20
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:57,388
I saw your wish video!

21
00:01:58,681 --> 00:02:00,475
-Are you threatening me?
-No.

22
00:02:00,975 --> 00:02:02,227
I'm trying to help you.

23
00:02:02,310 --> 00:02:05,021
You had no idea
Girigo would actually grant your wish.

24
00:02:06,481 --> 00:02:10,318
A wish you only made as a joke
got your friend killed.

25
00:02:10,860 --> 00:02:13,071
I know exactly how that feels.

26
00:02:13,154 --> 00:02:15,823
You're lonely and scared right now.

27
00:02:21,996 --> 00:02:24,374
I felt the same way
after I made my wish, Na-ri.

28
00:02:31,297 --> 00:02:33,466
Ha-joon's sister can help us.

29
00:02:33,967 --> 00:02:35,885
She helped me when I started acting weird.

30
00:02:39,389 --> 00:02:41,557
So, Na-ri…

31
00:02:44,519 --> 00:02:47,605
put that thing down.

32
00:02:50,024 --> 00:02:51,025
Okay?

33
00:03:00,827 --> 00:03:02,078
Na-ri.

34
00:03:14,257 --> 00:03:15,216
Na-ri.

35
00:03:20,722 --> 00:03:22,098
-Don't go!
-Why not?

36
00:03:30,481 --> 00:03:31,607
That's not a human.

37
00:03:49,083 --> 00:03:50,084
Na-ri!

38
00:03:51,044 --> 00:03:56,132
IF WISHES COULD KILL

39
00:04:11,898 --> 00:04:12,732
Please.

40
00:04:13,483 --> 00:04:14,317
Stop.

41
00:04:16,486 --> 00:04:17,445
Are you okay?

42
00:04:26,245 --> 00:04:27,080
Yeah.

43
00:04:27,705 --> 00:04:28,956
I'm okay.

44
00:04:32,126 --> 00:04:33,878
Geon-woo, what happened to your neck?

45
00:04:33,961 --> 00:04:35,046
Se-ah.

46
00:04:37,548 --> 00:04:39,258
I'm all good, thanks to you.

47
00:04:39,967 --> 00:04:40,968
So from now on,

48
00:04:41,677 --> 00:04:45,348
stop worrying about me
and look after yourself first, okay?

49
00:04:48,059 --> 00:04:50,770
Kids, where's a hospital nearby?

50
00:04:50,853 --> 00:04:51,771
The closest one.

51
00:04:51,854 --> 00:04:53,356
My aunt's hospital.

52
00:04:53,439 --> 00:04:55,274
Call your aunt. Let's head there now.

53
00:04:55,358 --> 00:04:56,734
Ha-joon's arm might be broken.

54
00:04:56,818 --> 00:04:59,695
They ran away from there.
How could they possibly go back?

55
00:05:00,530 --> 00:05:02,698
It should be okay
as long as we don't go in.

56
00:05:04,158 --> 00:05:05,243
He's right, Ha-joon.

57
00:05:05,993 --> 00:05:07,412
You two look badly hurt.

58
00:05:07,912 --> 00:05:09,414
Let's get to the hospital.

59
00:05:09,914 --> 00:05:13,751
SEORIN HOSPITAL

60
00:05:32,437 --> 00:05:34,689
-Yeah?
-Why aren't you getting out?

61
00:05:34,772 --> 00:05:37,525
I'm only slightly hurt. I'll be fine.
Go on without me.

62
00:05:37,608 --> 00:05:39,152
Slightly hurt? You're badly hurt.

63
00:05:40,319 --> 00:05:42,447
Go inside and get treated properly.

64
00:05:42,530 --> 00:05:44,115
Worried about your brother-in-law?

65
00:05:44,198 --> 00:05:46,576
Stop talking nonsense. Get out now.

66
00:05:46,659 --> 00:05:47,994
All right.

67
00:05:51,581 --> 00:05:52,999
-That hurts!
-Sorry, my bad.

68
00:05:53,082 --> 00:05:54,959
-Are you okay?
-Keep your distance.

69
00:05:56,794 --> 00:05:58,379
What's with you? That's gross!

70
00:05:58,463 --> 00:06:00,548
They look like family. It's nice.

71
00:06:00,631 --> 00:06:01,549
Right?

72
00:06:01,632 --> 00:06:02,467
Yeah.

73
00:06:03,092 --> 00:06:04,469
Just a moment, please.

74
00:06:05,011 --> 00:06:07,388
I'll quickly check
if you can be discharged.

75
00:06:07,472 --> 00:06:09,390
-Thank you.
-Okay. Thank you.

76
00:06:14,353 --> 00:06:17,690
-Hey, stop it.
-This made me lose my sense of distance.

77
00:06:19,567 --> 00:06:21,611
Haetsal sure is going to chew us out.

78
00:06:21,694 --> 00:06:23,529
You're worried about that, not my arm.

79
00:06:23,613 --> 00:06:25,156
That's why you stayed in the car.

80
00:06:25,239 --> 00:06:27,325
Why would you say that? That hurts.

81
00:06:27,408 --> 00:06:30,119
I had my reasons
for not getting out of the car.

82
00:06:30,203 --> 00:06:31,412
What? What were they?

83
00:06:32,538 --> 00:06:35,500
When a man and a woman are alone
in a car late at night…

84
00:06:35,583 --> 00:06:37,502
Jesus, you and your nonsense.

85
00:06:38,002 --> 00:06:40,755
I'm only worried
your one-sided crush will end miserably.

86
00:06:40,838 --> 00:06:43,674
Too bad you hurt your eye
instead of your mouth.

87
00:06:43,758 --> 00:06:44,884
Nope.

88
00:06:46,344 --> 00:06:47,970
I guess it's good I hurt my eye.

89
00:06:48,054 --> 00:06:49,263
Whatever, man.

90
00:06:53,976 --> 00:06:54,977
Brother-in-law.

91
00:06:55,978 --> 00:06:57,980
The power dwelling in Haetsal

92
00:06:58,064 --> 00:07:00,566
is beyond what a human body can endure.

93
00:07:00,650 --> 00:07:03,319
So we have to keep suppressing that power,

94
00:07:03,402 --> 00:07:05,571
using the divine spirit's ability
to see it.

95
00:07:06,239 --> 00:07:09,367
But what if I could

96
00:07:09,867 --> 00:07:12,286
also see that power,
just like the divine spirit?

97
00:07:18,167 --> 00:07:20,461
When you said
it was good you hurt your eye…

98
00:07:21,170 --> 00:07:23,047
Since I hurt my eye, I can see spirits.

99
00:07:24,423 --> 00:07:27,927
Haetsal's power is based on spirit,
so I should see it, right?

100
00:07:29,303 --> 00:07:33,224
Does this mean Ha-young will be able
to go outside like she used to?

101
00:07:33,307 --> 00:07:36,060
It might take some time to figure out how,

102
00:07:36,978 --> 00:07:39,397
but I promise I'll get her out.

103
00:07:39,480 --> 00:07:40,731
I can get her out.

104
00:07:40,815 --> 00:07:43,818
You mean it, brother-in-law? Really?

105
00:07:43,901 --> 00:07:45,403
-Brother-in-law?
-Never said that.

106
00:07:45,486 --> 00:07:46,946
That's what you called me.

107
00:07:47,530 --> 00:07:49,240
Why "brother-in-law" all of a sudden?

108
00:07:49,323 --> 00:07:51,701
I didn't call you that.
Stay back. It's hot.

109
00:07:52,535 --> 00:07:53,911
Slow down.

110
00:07:53,995 --> 00:07:56,581
Your brother-in-law with the injured eye
can't keep up.

111
00:07:56,664 --> 00:07:57,873
I gotta hurry, you know?

112
00:07:57,957 --> 00:08:01,502
If I'm going to see Ha-young,
I need to find the location first.

113
00:08:01,586 --> 00:08:02,753
Right, brother-in-law?

114
00:08:05,423 --> 00:08:06,424
Let's go.

115
00:08:06,507 --> 00:08:09,719
SEORIN HOSPITAL

116
00:08:12,471 --> 00:08:13,889
Are these all wish videos?

117
00:08:15,016 --> 00:08:15,850
Yeah.

118
00:08:17,226 --> 00:08:18,936
If our guess is correct,

119
00:08:19,812 --> 00:08:21,689
then this one, being the first posted,

120
00:08:23,065 --> 00:08:25,818
must have been the wish video
that made the app a curse.

121
00:08:34,493 --> 00:08:35,494
I'll play it now.

122
00:08:39,290 --> 00:08:40,416
Okay.

123
00:08:49,342 --> 00:08:51,302
Wondering what this crazy bitch is up to?

124
00:08:52,386 --> 00:08:54,597
I'll make the wish
just the way you told me.

125
00:08:55,556 --> 00:08:56,891
My wish is

126
00:08:58,100 --> 00:08:59,560
for all of you to die.

127
00:09:01,646 --> 00:09:04,523
I truly wish every one of you
would just drop dead.

128
00:09:04,607 --> 00:09:06,192
That's my wish.

129
00:09:21,165 --> 00:09:22,083
No doubt about it.

130
00:09:22,166 --> 00:09:23,876
Hyeong-wook and Do Hye-ryung…

131
00:09:26,253 --> 00:09:28,756
both died in the same way.

132
00:09:30,508 --> 00:09:31,759
The phone that filmed this…

133
00:09:34,261 --> 00:09:35,304
is the red phone.

134
00:09:48,984 --> 00:09:50,069
HAEJU INDUSTRIAL COMPLEX

135
00:09:50,152 --> 00:09:51,278
I got the location.

136
00:09:52,530 --> 00:09:53,698
Okay. Let's go.

137
00:09:58,661 --> 00:10:01,789
Do Hye-ryung filmed her wish video
at the marked location.

138
00:10:03,374 --> 00:10:06,335
You all remember the rainbow window
in the Polaroid photo, right?

139
00:10:06,419 --> 00:10:07,253
Yeah.

140
00:10:08,629 --> 00:10:10,840
Find the building with that window.

141
00:10:13,092 --> 00:10:16,429
The red phone is definitely
where that window is, right?

142
00:10:16,512 --> 00:10:18,264
It will definitely be there.

143
00:10:18,347 --> 00:10:21,016
Remember.
Only you can get it out of there.

144
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:25,104
You're the only one
connected to both the red phone and me.

145
00:10:28,691 --> 00:10:30,109
Don't worry, Se-ah.

146
00:10:30,192 --> 00:10:33,404
As long as you have the thread,
they can't touch you.

147
00:10:39,952 --> 00:10:42,621
But what's this rainbow window?

148
00:10:44,039 --> 00:10:46,459
Here. Take a look and give it to Se-ah.

149
00:10:46,542 --> 00:10:48,127
-Se-ah, hold onto that.
-Okay.

150
00:10:49,128 --> 00:10:52,757
So all we have to do
is find that red phone thing

151
00:10:52,840 --> 00:10:57,803
and bring it to Ha-young
for Se-ah to be completely okay, right?

152
00:10:57,887 --> 00:10:59,263
Of course.

153
00:11:01,474 --> 00:11:05,978
Geon-woo and Na-ri
will also go back to normal, right?

154
00:11:06,061 --> 00:11:06,896
Yeah.

155
00:11:07,855 --> 00:11:11,150
If we find the maehyung,
we should be able to save everyone cursed.

156
00:11:15,154 --> 00:11:15,988
Oh, that's right.

157
00:11:16,071 --> 00:11:20,326
Na-ri and I found something
when we went into the nurse's office.

158
00:11:24,205 --> 00:11:25,539
Laceration on the neck.

159
00:11:26,665 --> 00:11:27,500
"Kwon Si-won"?

160
00:11:28,709 --> 00:11:30,795
The shaman's child who went to Baekun?

161
00:11:31,962 --> 00:11:34,965
Brother-in-law, take a picture of this
and send it to your sister.

162
00:11:35,049 --> 00:11:35,883
Okay.

163
00:11:58,197 --> 00:11:59,448
GIRIGO
MAKE A WISH

164
00:12:03,702 --> 00:12:05,955
Fuck you, Do Hye-ryung!

165
00:12:07,623 --> 00:12:10,751
Let Do Hye-ryung's curse repeat itself.

166
00:12:10,835 --> 00:12:12,169
YOUR WISH HAS BEEN GRANTED

167
00:12:48,873 --> 00:12:50,541
HAEJU INDUSTRIAL COMPLEX

168
00:12:50,624 --> 00:12:51,625
Ten minutes out.

169
00:12:52,376 --> 00:12:53,210
Okay.

170
00:13:01,135 --> 00:13:02,595
Don't be scared.

171
00:13:02,678 --> 00:13:04,054
I'm here with you guys.

172
00:13:10,603 --> 00:13:12,646
BAEKUN-DONG
3 KM, 7 MINUTES

173
00:13:23,115 --> 00:13:24,700
Sure is creepy here.

174
00:13:30,039 --> 00:13:32,374
The route cannot be found.

175
00:13:38,380 --> 00:13:39,381
What?

176
00:13:42,843 --> 00:13:44,219
Straight ahead, right?

177
00:13:44,303 --> 00:13:46,889
Yes, straight ahead. Keep going.

178
00:13:58,901 --> 00:14:01,028
-Huh? What's wrong with this thing?
-What is it?

179
00:14:01,820 --> 00:14:03,489
My phone's GPS isn't working either.

180
00:14:05,658 --> 00:14:07,701
I think we turn right around here.

181
00:14:25,803 --> 00:14:27,554
What is this?

182
00:14:50,869 --> 00:14:52,287
Hold on tight!

183
00:15:05,300 --> 00:15:06,135
Are you okay?

184
00:15:08,887 --> 00:15:10,973
-Are you guys okay?
-Yes, I think we're okay.

185
00:15:45,299 --> 00:15:46,759
This is a nasty one.

186
00:15:49,845 --> 00:15:50,721
No!

187
00:15:57,644 --> 00:16:00,397
Remember.
Only you can get it out of there.

188
00:16:01,065 --> 00:16:05,360
You're the only one
connected to both the red phone and me.

189
00:16:08,697 --> 00:16:12,117
Unbind our wrongs
and ward off all ill-omened fate.

190
00:16:21,460 --> 00:16:22,961
Hey! Se-ah! Don't open the door!

191
00:16:24,880 --> 00:16:26,215
Don't open the door! No!

192
00:16:40,437 --> 00:16:41,271
Brother-in-law.

193
00:16:43,941 --> 00:16:45,692
Oh God! Brother-in-law!

194
00:17:01,333 --> 00:17:02,417
It's okay.

195
00:17:03,335 --> 00:17:05,170
No, don't say anything!

196
00:17:09,466 --> 00:17:10,843
You have to do it.

197
00:17:14,471 --> 00:17:16,056
Only you can do this.

198
00:17:17,349 --> 00:17:19,935
Find the red phone, so we

199
00:17:21,687 --> 00:17:24,565
can hurry back to Haetsal.

200
00:17:28,402 --> 00:17:29,945
It's okay. Don't cry.

201
00:17:32,865 --> 00:17:34,491
Brother-in-law, the knife…

202
00:17:34,575 --> 00:17:35,534
Okay.

203
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:37,828
Don't talk, okay?

204
00:17:40,372 --> 00:17:41,331
Here's the knife.

205
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:44,334
Geon-woo.

206
00:17:45,919 --> 00:17:47,921
When the spirit compass starts spinning,

207
00:17:48,005 --> 00:17:50,799
it means that those things
from the other side are nearby.

208
00:17:51,842 --> 00:17:55,053
So you need to keep an eye on that.
Keep Se-ah safe.

209
00:17:55,762 --> 00:17:56,597
Okay.

210
00:17:58,056 --> 00:17:59,016
I'll protect her.

211
00:18:00,017 --> 00:18:00,934
Okay.

212
00:18:03,270 --> 00:18:04,563
Go. Hurry.

213
00:18:05,397 --> 00:18:06,398
Go, quick.

214
00:18:08,358 --> 00:18:09,193
Se-ah, let's go.

215
00:18:09,276 --> 00:18:10,277
Please.

216
00:18:10,861 --> 00:18:11,778
Please.

217
00:18:17,326 --> 00:18:18,994
Oh God. Brother-in-law.

218
00:18:20,287 --> 00:18:21,121
Oh, 119.

219
00:18:22,289 --> 00:18:23,582
It's okay.

220
00:18:31,298 --> 00:18:32,674
Did the kids leave?

221
00:18:33,425 --> 00:18:34,843
Yeah, they left.

222
00:18:36,136 --> 00:18:38,555
Okay, then I need to rest now.

223
00:18:39,514 --> 00:18:41,850
Stop talking and stay with me!

224
00:18:43,143 --> 00:18:43,977
Okay.

225
00:18:44,937 --> 00:18:45,938
Brother-in-law.

226
00:18:46,897 --> 00:18:47,731
Yeah.

227
00:18:49,441 --> 00:18:52,402
Go to your sister. Go to Haetsal.

228
00:18:53,153 --> 00:18:54,446
What are you talking about?

229
00:18:54,947 --> 00:18:57,658
I called 119. Hang in there!

230
00:18:59,701 --> 00:19:00,577
Brother-in-law,

231
00:19:01,078 --> 00:19:03,747
you said you'd get my sister out of there!

232
00:19:05,249 --> 00:19:07,501
So don't die on me!

233
00:19:09,253 --> 00:19:10,254
"Brother-in-law."

234
00:19:13,423 --> 00:19:15,384
-Yes, brother-in-law.
-"Brother-in-law."

235
00:19:15,467 --> 00:19:16,551
Brother-in-law.

236
00:19:17,511 --> 00:19:19,763
No, you can't die.

237
00:19:24,851 --> 00:19:25,686
Se-ah!

238
00:19:30,482 --> 00:19:31,316
Look at this.

239
00:19:31,817 --> 00:19:33,151
This way, right?

240
00:19:33,652 --> 00:19:34,486
Yeah.

241
00:19:39,700 --> 00:19:40,534
This window.

242
00:19:41,243 --> 00:19:42,536
We just need to find it.

243
00:19:44,037 --> 00:19:44,871
Let's go.

244
00:19:58,927 --> 00:20:02,014
The rainbow window.

245
00:20:08,729 --> 00:20:09,938
Jesus.

246
00:20:10,522 --> 00:20:11,523
Damn it.

247
00:20:13,150 --> 00:20:14,151
Not here, I think.

248
00:20:24,369 --> 00:20:25,746
Not here either.

249
00:20:48,185 --> 00:20:49,186
Se-ah.

250
00:20:49,269 --> 00:20:51,188
Let me see that Polaroid photo again.

251
00:20:51,271 --> 00:20:52,105
Okay.

252
00:20:57,277 --> 00:20:59,988
We don't have much time.
Let's split up and look for it.

253
00:21:00,489 --> 00:21:02,699
-Okay.
-I'll go this way and look for it.

254
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:04,034
Be careful.

255
00:21:04,534 --> 00:21:05,369
You too.

256
00:21:10,916 --> 00:21:13,585
Penetrating lower-right abdominal wound.
Heavy bleeding.

257
00:21:14,169 --> 00:21:15,712
You need to live, brother-in-law.

258
00:21:24,471 --> 00:21:26,556
Expect heavy bleeding. Prep a transfusion.

259
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:27,891
I'll remove it now.

260
00:21:28,392 --> 00:21:29,226
Suction!

261
00:21:29,309 --> 00:21:30,685
Not this window either.

262
00:21:32,229 --> 00:21:33,438
Not this one either.

263
00:21:41,822 --> 00:21:44,199
Geon-woo! I found it!

264
00:21:44,282 --> 00:21:45,659
Huh? You found it?

265
00:21:53,667 --> 00:21:55,252
You found it? Where?

266
00:22:14,187 --> 00:22:15,063
Ha-young.

267
00:22:16,648 --> 00:22:19,651
Brother-in-law is in the operating room.

268
00:22:20,777 --> 00:22:22,821
He was trying to protect us.

269
00:22:22,904 --> 00:22:25,031
No, Ha-joon. Don't think like that.

270
00:22:25,532 --> 00:22:28,410
It's not your fault,
and the surgery will go well.

271
00:22:33,874 --> 00:22:35,292
I'll go over there.

272
00:22:35,375 --> 00:22:36,209
Okay.

273
00:22:47,179 --> 00:22:48,388
These stairs are broken.

274
00:22:54,478 --> 00:22:55,687
Geon-woo, over here!

275
00:23:18,293 --> 00:23:20,420
Se-ah, be careful.

276
00:23:21,963 --> 00:23:22,797
Okay.

277
00:23:31,681 --> 00:23:32,516
Let's go.

278
00:23:38,146 --> 00:23:38,980
Hey.

279
00:23:40,357 --> 00:23:42,651
Hold on. I'll go first.

280
00:23:44,152 --> 00:23:45,320
No, it's okay.

281
00:23:45,820 --> 00:23:46,988
I'll go first.

282
00:24:10,971 --> 00:24:11,972
No other choice.

283
00:24:13,974 --> 00:24:15,934
What are you doing? Huh? It's dangerous.

284
00:24:17,727 --> 00:24:18,812
What are you doing?

285
00:24:21,731 --> 00:24:22,899
Hey, you're gonna jump?

286
00:24:24,067 --> 00:24:25,402
It's barely a gap.

287
00:24:28,029 --> 00:24:29,781
Still, let me jump across instead.

288
00:24:33,660 --> 00:24:35,495
I'm the only one who can find the phone.

289
00:24:36,830 --> 00:24:37,831
Don't worry.

290
00:24:47,882 --> 00:24:49,175
Se-ah, are you okay?

291
00:24:52,345 --> 00:24:53,179
Yeah.

292
00:24:53,930 --> 00:24:55,056
I'm okay.

293
00:24:56,349 --> 00:24:58,435
Geon-woo, it's dangerous. Stay there.

294
00:25:01,313 --> 00:25:03,315
What are you saying?
I'm coming across too.

295
00:25:03,398 --> 00:25:04,274
Geon-woo.

296
00:25:04,774 --> 00:25:05,900
I'm really okay.

297
00:25:06,401 --> 00:25:08,111
I'll check and be right back.

298
00:25:39,851 --> 00:25:40,852
Se-ah.

299
00:26:27,440 --> 00:26:28,274
Na-ri.

300
00:26:29,526 --> 00:26:30,527
Na-ri!

301
00:26:33,405 --> 00:26:34,531
Se-ah!

302
00:26:47,085 --> 00:26:48,211
Lim Na-ri!

303
00:26:53,758 --> 00:26:55,385
You're not going anywhere.

304
00:26:55,885 --> 00:26:57,178
I won't let you go.

305
00:26:57,262 --> 00:26:58,221
Please!

306
00:26:58,304 --> 00:27:00,056
Come to your senses!

307
00:27:06,479 --> 00:27:08,898
Close your eyes
and take a moment to think.

308
00:27:09,482 --> 00:27:11,359
"The whole world is the mat."

309
00:27:11,443 --> 00:27:12,569
"I can do this."

310
00:27:13,319 --> 00:27:14,738
Picture that,

311
00:27:14,821 --> 00:27:17,198
and when you open your eyes,
run like crazy and jump.

312
00:27:17,282 --> 00:27:18,366
I can do this.

313
00:28:17,634 --> 00:28:18,468
Na-ri.

314
00:28:24,724 --> 00:28:25,558
Na…

315
00:29:31,541 --> 00:29:32,792
Na-ri.

316
00:29:35,670 --> 00:29:38,214
Na-ri, it's you, right?

317
00:29:46,639 --> 00:29:49,559
How did we end up like this?

318
00:29:55,857 --> 00:29:57,734
Na-ri.

319
00:30:02,196 --> 00:30:03,031
Na-ri.

320
00:30:04,949 --> 00:30:05,992
Let's get out of here.

321
00:30:11,247 --> 00:30:13,291
Let's go back together.

322
00:30:13,833 --> 00:30:14,667
Okay?

323
00:30:15,168 --> 00:30:16,711
No.

324
00:30:18,755 --> 00:30:21,049
I told you we can't get out of here.

325
00:30:23,801 --> 00:30:25,637
I told you I won't let you go.

326
00:30:30,642 --> 00:30:31,476
No!

327
00:30:40,985 --> 00:30:42,236
Se-ah!

328
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:43,863
Se-ah, snap out of it!

329
00:30:46,407 --> 00:30:47,533
Se-ah.

330
00:30:47,617 --> 00:30:48,660
Se-ah!

331
00:30:48,743 --> 00:30:49,577
No.

332
00:30:51,120 --> 00:30:51,955
Se-ah…

333
00:34:35,094 --> 00:34:37,847
Subtitle translation by: Sung In Jang
